main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects over Tucson, Arizona in 1949. Objects observed include a white, round object, a balloon changing in shape, and a fast-moving, highly reflective object.
interesting points: One sighting reported a white, round object like a football bladder changing to flat, reflecting sunlight and drifting along, before disappearing after climbing.
Another report mentioned an object estimated at five miles per second by radar, exhibiting extremely high speed and high altitude flight.
The observers were described as credible and included a truck driver, an electrical store employee, and military personnel.
The sightings did not demonstrate a clear explanation or provide physical evidence. They involved maneuvering at high speed, rapid climbing, and hovering.
There were also reports of electromagnetic effects on aircraft and the Interference with the operation of aircraft, as well as concerns about the impact on navigation and visibility.
witnesses: credible witnesses including civilians, military personnel, and pilots
photographs: no photographs available in the report
